This completes the proof of Theorem 1. 

Proof of Theorem 2.: By the Hoeffding's inequality, the following inequality holds with at least \(1-\delta\):

\[\left|\mathcal{L}_{\text{avg}}-\hat{\mathcal{L}}_{\text{avg}}\right|\leq C \cdot\sqrt{\frac{2\log(1/\delta)}{n}}.\] (21)

Accordingly, the expected average loss is bounded with probability \(1-\delta\) as follows:

\[\hat{\mathcal{L}}_{\text{avg}}-C\cdot\sqrt{\frac{2\log(1/\delta)}{n}}\leq \mathcal{L}_{\text{avg}}\leq\hat{\mathcal{L}}_{\text{avg}}+C\cdot\sqrt{\frac{2 \log(1/\delta)}{n}}.\] (22)

